main event: On 17 October 1952, there was a report of unidentified flying objects in Killeen, Texas, observed by reliable sources. The objects were disc-shaped, exhibited bright lights, and moved at high speeds without leaving a contrail.
interesting points: The sightings were made by several reliable observers, and the objects were observed to be disc-shaped with bright lights, moving at speeds estimated to be in excess of 600 mph.
The objects were seen at an altitude estimated to be between 2,000 and 5,000 feet and appeared to follow a southwest to northeast direction.
No sound was heard, and there was no visible indication of the method of propulsion. The objects did not leave a contrail.
Despite the observations, local authorities failed to reveal any corroborating observations or have knowledge of any aircraft flights or searchlights being used in the vicinity at the time.

The report also includes a summary of information received concerning sightings of unidentified flying objects in the Killeen, Texas area, stating that no technical analysis had been made and that the sightings were by reliable observers.
